data.name: Gourmet Truffle Beef Wellington
data.quickTastyDescription: A luxurious and flavorful dish featuring tender beef wrapped in flaky pastry, enhanced with earthy truffle notes, served alongside creamy garlic mashed potatoes and perfectly roasted asparagus.
detailedCookingInstructions: Season the beef tenderloin with salt and pepper, then sear in a pan over high heat until browned on all sides. Set aside to cool.
Finely chop the mushrooms and sauté in the same pan until golden and all moisture has evaporated. Allow to cool slightly, then mix with truffle pate.
Lay out the prosciutto slices on a sheet of plastic wrap, overlapping slightly. Spread the mushroom mixture over the prosciutto.
Place the beef on top of the mushroom-prosciutto layer and roll tightly using the plastic wrap. Chill in the refrigerator for 15 minutes.
Roll out the puff pastry sheets, and wrap them around the beef, sealing the edges with beaten egg. Brush the outside of the pastry with the remaining egg wash.
Place the wrapped beef on a baking sheet and bake for 25-30 minutes, or until the pastry is golden and the beef reaches desired doneness. Rest for 10 minutes before slicing.
For the mashed potatoes, boil the potatoes in salted water until tender. Drain and mash with butter, milk, garlic, and salt to taste.
Toss the asparagus with olive oil, salt, and pepper. Roast in the oven for 10-12 minutes until tender.
data.detailedName: Gourmet Truffle-Infused Beef Wellington with Creamy Garlic Mashed Potatoes and Roasted Asparagus
data.modifiersForBase: Infused with truffle flavors and served with garlic mashed potatoes and roasted asparagus.
